title: JUIâ€™s Candidate Waheed Gul wins PK-20 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Jamat-e-Islami Pakistan (JUI) Candidate Waheed Gul has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-20, Bajour-II by securing 13,039 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up An Independent Candidate Anwar Zeb Khan who bagged 12,903 votes.
Overall voters turn-out remained 31.6 per cent.
